{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Edit tool window"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 21], "level": 0}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [88, 177], "text": ["See ", {"text": ["customizing the shelf"], "fullpath": "/shelf/customize", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/customize"}, " for information on rearranging the shelf."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [182, 359], "text": ["To make a shelf item that creates a node or group of nodes, you don\u2019t need to script the item yourself. Just drag the node or nodes from the network editor onto the shelf."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "tip", "extent": [177, 182]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "extent": [359, 498], "text": ["In the shelf, right click the tab background and choose ", {"text": ["New tool"], "type": "ui"}, ", or right-click an existing icon and choose ", {"text": ["Edit tool"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "extent": [498, 694], "text": ["Set the item\u2019s ", {"text": ["Name"], "type": "ui"}, " (an identifier that must be unique across all tabs), and ", {"text": ["Label"], "type": "ui"}, " (the human-readable label that will appear in the tooltip and when the shelf is set to display text)."]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Creating and editing shelf items"], "extent": [49, 88], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [734, 1082], "text": ["The ", {"text": ["Tools"], "type": "ui"}, " tab of the ", {"text": ["type properties window"], "fullpath": "/ref/windows/optype", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/windows/optype"}, " lets you specify the options for item(s) that added to the ", {"text": ["tab menu"], "fullpath": "/basics/tabmenu", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/basics/tabmenu"}, " for a ", {"text": ["digital asset"], "fullpath": "/assets/index", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/assets/"}, ". This lets you, for example, write a script, and specify a different submenu name (by default all digital assets show up in a submenu named \"Digital Assets\")."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Embedding tools in digital assets"], "extent": [694, 734], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1114, 1379], "text": ["The ", {"text": [".shelf"], "type": "code"}, " file to save the tool into. The default is ", {"text": ["$HOME/houdiniX.X/toolbar/default.shelf"], "type": "code"}, ", which makes the tool available to you. To make the tool available for other people to put on their shelf, add it to a ", {"text": [".shelf"], "type": "code"}, " file in some central location."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1379, 1574], "text": ["Any shelf files you save should be in $HOUDINI_PATH in a ", {"text": ["toolbar"], "type": "code"}, " folder, or in a directory in the the ", {"text": ["$HOUDINI_TOOLBAR_PATH"], "type": "code"}, " if it is defined. Shelf files must have a ", {"text": [".shelf"], "type": "code"}, " extension."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1574, 1718], "text": ["You can load a ", {"text": [".shelf"], "type": "code"}, " file from the path by choosing it from the ", {"text": ["Shelf Sets"], "type": "ui"}, " submenu of the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/ref/windows/BUTTONS/pane_menu", "scheme": "Smallicon", "type": "link", "value": "BUTTONS/pane_menu"}, " shelf menu."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [1104, 1114], "text": ["Save to"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Window controls"], "extent": [1082, 1104], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1757, 1930], "text": ["Internal name of the shelf item. This must be unique across all loaded\n    shelf tools. Must start with a letter, can contain letters, numbers,\n    and/or underscores."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Name"], "attrs": {"id": "name"}, "extent": [1736, 1743], "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1952, 2140], "text": ["The human-readable name of the shelf item, appears in the\n    ", {"text": ["tab menu"], "fullpath": "/basics/tabmenu", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/basics/tabmenu"}, ". The label should be\n    relatively short (two to four words) but as descriptive as possible."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Label"], "attrs": {"id": "label"}, "extent": [1930, 1937], "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2931, 3017], "text": ["A reference to an icon file (SVG or image), in one of the following formats:"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3017, 3102], "text": ["An ", {"text": ["opdef:"], "type": "code"}, " path to an embedded file in the asset\u2019s ", {"fragment": "#extra", "text": ["extra files"], "value": "#extra", "fullpath": "/ref/windows/optype#extra", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3102, 3164], "text": ["A file path or URL for a file containing the icon."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3164, 3254], "text": ["The name of a built-in Houdini icon. For example, ", {"text": ["OBJ_geo"], "type": "code"}, " or ", {"text": ["SHELF_candle"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3254, 3463], "text": ["Click the chooser button next to the field to browse for an icon. You can browse for a file on disk, or click ", {"text": ["opdef:/"], "type": "code"}, " in the chooser to browse embedded files, or ", {"text": ["hicon:/"], "type": "code"}, " to browse built-in icons."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3463, 3720], "text": ["If you choose a file on disk and ", {"text": ["Embed icon in operator"], "type": "ui"}, " is on, when you click ", {"text": ["Accept"], "type": "ui"}, " Houdini will automatically copy the file into the asset\u2019s ", {"fragment": "#extra", "text": ["extra files"], "value": "#extra", "fullpath": "/ref/windows/optype#extra", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " and replace the ", {"text": ["Icon"], "type": "ui"}, " field with an ", {"text": ["opdef:"], "type": "code"}, " reference to the embedded icon."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Icon"], "attrs": {"id": "icon"}, "extent": [2906, 2912], "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Options tab"], "extent": [1718, 1736], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2198, 2439], "text": ["The language of the script. This lets you write this script in HScript, but doing so does not offer any of the advantages of Python, and the script cannot be selection/context aware. We strongly encourage you to use Python instead."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [2180, 2198], "text": ["Script language"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2456, 2675], "text": ["Click ", {"text": ["Launch"], "type": "ui"}, " to edit the script in an external editing program (defined by the ", {"text": ["$EDITOR"], "type": "code"}, " environment variable). When you save and quit the external editor, your changes will appear in the Edit tool window."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [2439, 2456], "text": ["External editor"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2683, 2795], "text": ["Enter the script to run when the user clicks the shelf item. See ", {"text": ["writing a tool script"], "fullpath": "/hom/tool_script", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/hom/tool_script"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [2675, 2683], "text": ["Script"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Script tab"], "extent": [2163, 2180], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [2810, 2942], "text": ["You can write or paste ", {"text": ["wiki-formatted"], "fullpath": "/help/format", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/help/format"}, " help for the the item here, or specify a URL the help should be loaded from."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [2942, 3196], "text": ["This help is displayed when the user hovers over the item and presses ", {"keys": ["F1"], "text": null, "type": "keys"}, ". When you write the help in wiki format, Houdini uses its \"summary\" text as the item\u2019s tooltip (see the ", {"text": ["wiki format documentation"], "fullpath": "/help/format", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/help/format"}, " for information on summaries)."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Help tab"], "extent": [2795, 2810], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [3214, 3401], "text": ["The options on this tab control on which tab menus (in which network contexts) the item appears, when the user opens the ", {"text": ["tab menu"], "fullpath": "/basics/tabmenu", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/basics/tabmenu"}, " in the viewer or network editor."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [3401, 3663], "text": ["The ", {"text": ["Tab submenu path"], "type": "ui"}, " controls which sub-menu of the tab menu the item appears in. You aren\u2019t restricted to the submenus containing the original Houdini tools \u2013 you can type a new name here and Houdini will create the corresponding submenu on the tab menu."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Context tab"], "extent": [3196, 3214], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [3681, 3918], "text": ["This tab lets you specify hotkeys for the item. You can give the item a ", {"text": ["Global"], "type": "ui"}, " hotkey that works everywhere, and/or a hotkey that only works when the mouse is in the network editor pane, scene view pane, or compositing view pane. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [3918, 4032], "text": ["Refer to the ", {"text": ["Hotkey editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/windows/hotkey", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/windows/hotkey"}, " to avoid possible conflicts with existing hotkeys."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Hotkeys tab"], "extent": [3663, 3681], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [4041, 4055], "text": [{"text": ["HOM"], "fullpath": "/hom", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/hom"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [4032, 4041], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "included": ["/ref/windows/optype"], "type": "root", "attrs": {"helpid": "h.shelf.edittool"}, "title": ["Edit tool window"]}